      "span_text": "Briefly, mononuclear cells were seeded at a density of approximately 1.8 Â 10 5 /cm 2 on 24-well plates coated with 200 mg/ml type-I rat collagen (BD Biosciences, Bedford, MA, USA) and grown in Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium (DMEM) supplemented with 10% fetal calf serum (FCS), 2 mM L-glutamine and antibiotics (100 mg/ml streptomycin and 10 000 U/ml penicillin), all purchased from Biological Industries (Beit Haemek, Afula, Israel).",
